-- 
Intesa Plans to Simplify Bank Structure, Messaggero Reports

-- B y   A r m o r e l   K e n n a
-- 
2011-08-04T06:07:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-04/intesa-plans-to-simplify-bank-structure-messaggero-reports.html
Intesa Sanpaolo SpA (ISP)  plans to simplify
the bank structure, merging units in the Italian regions of
Umbria, Marche and Lazio, daily Il Messaggero reported, without
saying where it got the information.  Intesa may reduce the number of banks controlled by its
Banca dei Territori unit in the areas to 15 from 22, reducing
costs,  according to the Italian newspaper. The management may
approve the plan tomorrow, the daily reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Armorel Kenna in Milan at 
 akenna@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Celeste Perri at 
 cperri@bloomberg.net  